As per the validation performed by the OS team, the /sftp_home filesystem is currently mounted using NFSv3 and is dependent on the rpcbind service for mount and locking operations. The validation also confirmed that mounting the share using NFSv4 was unsuccessful.
Since the current implementation relies on NFSv3, disabling the rpcbind service may impact NFS connectivity and application functionality.
Regarding the suggestion to use SFTP instead of NFS, SFTP is a file transfer mechanism whereas NFS provides shared filesystem access. Migration from NFS to SFTP would require application-level and operational changes and cannot be implemented as an OS-level configuration change.